===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# [[married]] [[woman]], [[matron]]
#: {{zh-x|少婦|young married woman}}
# [[woman]]
#: {{zh-x|婦孺|women and children}}
#* {{zh-x|婦 無 公事、休 其 蠶-織。|So a '''woman''', who has nothing to do with public affairs, leaves her silk-worms and weaving.|ref=Shijing}}
#* {{zh-x|無 自 廣 以 狹 人，匹夫 匹婦，不 獲 自 盡{jǐn}，民主 罔 與 成 厥 功。|Do not think yourself so large as to deem others small. If ordinary men and '''women''' do not find the opportunity to give full development to their ability, the people's lord will be without the proper aids to complete his merit.'|ref=WGWSS}}
# [[wife]]
#: {{zh-x|夫婦|husband and wife}}
#* {{zh-x|使君 自 有 婦，^羅 ^敷 自 有 夫！|You have your own '''wife''', Prefect, Luofu has her own husband!|ref={{lang|zh|陌上桑}} ({{lw|zh|s:日出東南隅行 (豔歌羅敷行)|日出東南隅行}}) "Ballad about Sunrise at the southeast corner", included in ''{{w|New Songs from the Jade Terrace}}'' ({{lw|zh|玉臺新詠}}) {{defdate|circa 6th century}}. [http://www.silkqin.com/02qnpu/29lqxs/lq12mss.htm Translated] by Anne Birrell|CL}}

